Module contents¶

Inference package initialization.

The package is organized into layered subpackages:

  • src.inference.domains – task-specific inference loops (math/carpark/crossword/summarize).

  • src.inference.utils – shared helpers, backends, and registries.

  • src.inference.runners and src.inference.cli – reusable runner logic plus thin CLIs.

  • src.inference.gateways – remote math runners (Azure, OpenRouter, Portkey).

Only lightweight, stable symbols are re-exported here to keep import-time dependencies minimal.

class src.inference.GenerationLimits(batch_size: int, num_samples: int, think_cap: int, answer_cap: int)[source]¶

Bases: object

Shared cap and sampling-count configuration used by multiple runners.

Parameters:

  • batch_size – Number of examples per batch.

  • num_samples – Number of samples to generate per problem.

  • think_cap – Token cap for <think> generations.

  • answer_cap – Token cap for <answer> generations.

answer_cap: int¶
batch_size: int¶
num_samples: int¶
think_cap: int¶
class src.inference.SamplingConfigBase(temperature: float = 0.0, top_p: float = 0.95, entropy_mode: str = 'reconsider', eos_ids: List[int] | None = None)[source]¶

Bases: object

Shared sampling defaults used by multiple inference configs.

This centralizes common fields so that task-specific configs (math, crossword, etc.) can extend it without duplicating dataclass bodies.

eos_ids: List[int] | None = None¶
